"QuickCommerce MIS Dashboard (Excel + Power Query)"

'Project Overview'

This project demonstrates an end-to-end automated MIS dashboard built using Microsoft Excel and Power Query. The objective is to transform raw operational data into a structured master dataset and generate meaningful business insights through interactive dashboards.

'Objective'

To clean, transform, and consolidate raw order data into a single master dataset and build dynamic KPIs and MIS dashboards for performance analysis.

'Tools Used'

Microsoft Excel

Power Query

Pivot Tables

Slicers

'Key Features'

Automated data transformation using Power Query

Multiple raw data sheets combined into a single master dataset using Power Query

Code-to-name mapping using reference tables

SLA vs Actual delivery performance analysis

Dynamic KPI calculations using Pivot Tables

Interactive MIS dashboard using slicers


"Data Transformation Process"

The data preparation process was automated using Power Query:

Importing multiple raw data sheets

Combining multiple sheets into one consolidated dataset

Cleaning and removing inconsistent or null values

Converting data types and formatting columns

Mapping reference codes to readable values

Creating a structured master dataset for analysis


'Automation Flow'

Raw Data → Multiple Sheets → Power Query Combine & Transform → Master Sheet → KPI & MIS Dashboard


'How to Use'

Download the Excel file

Open the workbook

Go to Data → Refresh All

Use slicers to explore insights and filter dashboard results

'Disclaimer'

This is a self-learning project built using simulated data for educational and portfolio purposes.
